Razavi-Bench Dataset License

This repository contains multiple categories of material with different
copyright ownership and licensing terms.

1. Original source questions and figures

The benchmark questions and source figures are based on Behzad Razavi,
"Analog Design Experiments With AI--Part 1" and "Analog Design Experiments
With AI--Part 2", published in IEEE Solid-State Circuits Magazine.

Copyright in the original articles, questions, figures, and other source
materials remains with their respective rights holders, including Behzad
Razavi and/or IEEE, as applicable. These materials are included or adapted
in Razavi-Bench with permission from Behzad Razavi for public release of the
benchmark and associated AI model responses.

Unless otherwise stated, this repository does not grant additional rights to
third-party copyrighted IEEE/Razavi source material beyond the permission
under which it is included here.

2. Benchmark curation and derived dataset structure

The task organization, metadata, evaluation packaging, cleaned transcripts,
score tables, documentation, and other original curation work in this
repository are Copyright (c) 2026 Zhang Tuoken.

To the extent copyright or database rights exist in these materials, they
are licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License
(CC BY 4.0).

You may obtain a copy of CC BY 4.0 at:

https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

3. AI model outputs

The AI model responses are published for research, reproducibility, and
independent re-evaluation. To the extent Zhang Tuoken owns or controls any
rights in the collected model outputs, those rights are licensed under CC BY
4.0.

Model outputs are generated by third-party AI systems and should not be
interpreted as endorsed by Behzad Razavi, IEEE, OpenAI, Google, Anthropic, or
any other model provider.

4. Code

Any code in this repository, including scripts for formatting, evaluation, or
analysis, is licensed separately under the MIT License in LICENSE-CODE unless
a file states otherwise.
